Separation¶

Loading model from file¶

Currently, ChimeraNetModel wraps partial thing of keras' model.
This procedure might be wrapped on future release.

[1]:

%%capture
import librosa
from keras.models import load_model
from keras.utils import CustomObjectScope
from chimeranet.model import ChimeraNetModel

# parameters for loading model
time = 0.75
sr, n_fft, hop_length, n_mels = 16000, 512, 128, 96
n_channels = 2
d_embedding = 20

T, F = librosa.core.time_to_frames(time, sr, hop_length), n_mels
cm = ChimeraNetModel(T, F, n_channels, d_embedding)

with CustomObjectScope({
    '_loss_deepclustering': cm.loss_deepclustering(),
    '_loss_mask': cm.loss_mask(),
}):
    model = load_model('example-model.h5')

Loading audio and prediction¶

[2]:

%%capture
import numpy as np
from chimeranet.window_util import split_window
# load audio
audio, _ = librosa.core.load(librosa.util.example_audio_file(), sr=sr)
audio = audio[:100000]
spec, phase = librosa.core.magphase(
    librosa.core.stft(audio, n_fft, hop_length)
)
mel_basis = librosa.filters.mel(sr, n_fft, n_mels)
mel_spec = np.dot(mel_basis, spec)
# split into windows
x = split_window(mel_spec**2, T).transpose((0, 2, 1))
# prediction
y_embedding, y_mask = model.predict(x)

Reconstruction from mask prediction¶

[4]:

from numpy.linalg import pinv
from chimeranet.postprocessing import from_mask
from chimeranet.window_util import merge_windows_mean
import IPython.display as ipd

mask_windows = from_mask(y_mask)
masks = merge_windows_mean(mask_windows)[:, :, :mel_spec.shape[1]]
mel_basis_inv = pinv(mel_basis)

mask = masks[0]
pred_spec = np.dot(mel_basis_inv, mask*mel_spec)
out_audio = librosa.core.istft(pred_spec*phase, hop_length)
ipd.Audio(out_audio, rate=sr)

[4]:

[5]:

mask = masks[1]
pred_spec = np.dot(mel_basis_inv, mask*mel_spec)
out_audio = librosa.core.istft(pred_spec*phase, hop_length)
ipd.Audio(out_audio, rate=sr)

Reconstruction from embedding prediction¶

[6]:

from chimeranet.postprocessing import from_embedding
from chimeranet.window_util import merge_windows_most_common

mask_windows = from_embedding(y_embedding, n_channels)
masks = merge_windows_most_common(mask_windows)[:, :, :mel_spec.shape[1]]

mask = masks[0]
pred_spec = np.dot(mel_basis_inv, mask*mel_spec)
out_audio = librosa.core.istft(pred_spec*phase, hop_length)
ipd.Audio(out_audio, rate=sr)
